definitions.definition: A ringlike band of muscle that surrounds a bodily opening (such as the anus or the openings of the stomach ), constricting and relaxing as required for normal physiological functioning.
examples: the iris sphincter in the eye

main_definition: ( anatomy ) A ringlike band of muscle that surrounds a bodily opening (such as the anus or the openings of the stomach ), constricting and relaxing as required for normal physiological functioning.
